summary: The person on a hospital bed I was looking at was... miserable. Their eyes were almost closed like they were trying to escape...
body:
The person on a hospital bed I was looking at was… miserable. Their eyes were almost closed like they were trying to escape the light of a faze. Their hair was messy and scanty which made their face look haggard. The person opened their mouth willing to say something but the only thing I could hear was a wheeze. 
“What has happened to them, doc?” I asked a tall man who stood next to the bed and apparently was his doctor. 
“They’re a victim of the 2019 hiatus”
I gasped. I wasn’t expecting to hear this. 
“They’ve been through a lot, haven’t they?” 
“Not many people survived it” The doctor nodded.
I cast my eye on them, their shrunken cheeks and hands…
They were a true hero.
